## 2. Folder structure вҖ” **`xotel_code/getafix/trunk/ansible`** (OTel / shared Ansible)

Ansible for things like the **OTel collector** lives under **Getafix**, not `exotel_configs`. A common layout (matches the idea of **`roles/otel-collector`** on a branch like **`feature/otel-collector`**):

```text
xotel_code/
в””в”Җв”Җ getafix/
    в””в”Җв”Җ trunk/
        в””в”Җв”Җ ansible/
            в”ңв”Җв”Җ ansible.cfg              # roles_path, inventory, defaults
            в”ңв”Җв”Җ otel.yml                 # top-level playbook (example name)
            в”ңв”Җв”Җ hosts                    # default inventory
            в”ңв”Җв”Җ hosts.qa                 # optional: env-specific inventory
            в”ңв”Җв”Җ env-vars/
            в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ qa                   # vars loaded per env (see playbook)
            в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ prod
            в””в”Җв”Җ roles/
                в””в”Җв”Җ otel-collector/      # role you develop on feature branch
                    в”ңв”Җв”Җ defaults/
                    в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ main.yml     # default ports, memory, exporters, etc.
                    в”ңв”Җв”Җ tasks/
                    в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ main.yml     # install binary, template config, systemd
                    в”ңв”Җв”Җ handlers/
                    в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ main.yml     # restart collector
                    в”ңв”Җв”Җ meta/
                    в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ main.yml
                    в”ңв”Җв”Җ templates/
                    в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ otel-config.yaml.j2
                    в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ otel-collector.service.j2
                    в””в”Җв”Җ vars/
                        в”ңв”Җв”Җ qa             # optional extra overrides per env
                        в””в”Җв”Җ prod
```

**Branching (how you explain it)**

- Day-to-day work on the role: branch **`feature/otel-collector`** (or your teamвҖҷs name) вҖ” same paths under `trunk/ansible`, you commit role + playbook changes there.
- When stable, merge into **`trunk`** (or `master`) so other playbooks and CI use the updated role.

**Local clone in this workspace (same idea, shorter path):** `otel/otel-ansible/` вҶ’ use it as the **mirror** when you study or demo.

**What this is for**

| Piece | Plain meaning |
|-------|----------------|
| **`ansible.cfg`** | Tells Ansible where **`roles/`** and **inventory** live. |
| **`otel.yml`** | Which hosts run which **roles** (e.g. `otel-collector`). |
| **`hosts` / `hosts.qa`** | Which servers get OTel; **groups** match `hosts:` in the playbook. |
| **`env-vars/qa`**, **`env-vars/prod`** | Variables for **qa** vs **prod** (endpoints, memory, feature flags). |
| **`roles/otel-collector`** | All steps to install and run the collector **reusably**. |

