## 3. Folder structure вҖ” Voicebot **Ansible** on-prem (`setup-configs`) вҖ” unchanged

This is the **Ansible** world for Voicebot (VMs). You keep **one folder per environment** under `setup-configs/`.

```text
voicebot_scripts/common_ansibles/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ roles/                          # shared Ansible roles
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ redis/
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ postgresql_replication/
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ ...
в”ңв”Җв”Җ setup-configs/
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ prod/
в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ inventory.yml
в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ ansible.cfg
в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ application-versions.txt
в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ group_vars/
в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ all.yml
в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ <role_name>/main.yml
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ dev/
в”Ӯ       в””в”Җв”Җ ... (same shape)
в””в”Җв”Җ sync-config.py                  # merge setup + roles вҶ’ bundle вҶ’ optional S3
```

**Flow in simple steps**

1. Edit **`setup-configs/prod/`** (IPs, versions, vault secrets).
2. **`sync-config.py`** builds the bundle and can **upload to S3**.
3. **Jump server** runs **bootstrap** вҶ’ downloads bundle from S3.
4. Run **`deploy_dbs.sh`** / **`deploy_applications.sh`** вҶ’ Ansible targets **DB / app VMs**.

**How it relates to Getafix:** **Voicebot** = per-customer/per-env **`setup-configs`** + sync + jump server. **Getafix `trunk/ansible`** = shared automation (e.g. **otel-collector** role) that can be **reused** or **vendored** the way your org does it вҖ” different repo root, same Ansible concepts.

